[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: 6. Storage (LittleFS)

[GRAMMAR]
ELEMENTS:
- TAG: REQUIREMENT
  FIELDS:
  - TITLE: UID
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: STATUS
    TYPE: SingleChoice(Draft, Active, Deprecated)
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: TAGS
    TYPE: Tag
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: STATEMENT
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: VERIFICATION
    TYPE: SingleChoice(Test, Inspection, Analysis, Review)
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: RATIONALE
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: REFS
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: False

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-5000
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Storage, Logs
STATEMENT: The firmware shall write mission log entries to ``/logs/mission_<script_name>.txt`` at a rate not exceeding 1 entry per LOG_RATE_MS (100 ms). Each entry shall be a single line in the format: ``t_ms=<elapsed>,state=<name>,<field>=<value>,...``  Log entries shall be appended; existing log files shall not be truncated on activation of the same script.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: AMS-2 / config.h LOG_RATE_MS. A bounded write rate limits LittleFS flash wear and prevents log file growth from consuming the entire filesystem partition during long missions.
REFS: docs/standards/ams_standard.md AMS-2, src/config.h LOG_RATE_MS, LOG_DIR

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-5001
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Storage, API, Download
STATEMENT: Mission log file download via GET /api/storage/download shall stream file content in chunks not exceeding DOWNLOAD_CHUNK_SIZE (512 bytes) without loading the entire file into SRAM. The endpoint shall support the "file" query parameter specifying the filename within /logs/.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: REST-12.2 / config.h. Chunked streaming avoids allocating a static buffer large enough for the whole log file, which could overflow the 512 KB SRAM on long missions.
REFS: docs/standards/apirest_standard.md REST-12.2, src/config.h DOWNLOAD_CHUNK_SIZE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-5002
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Storage, Security
STATEMENT: The REST API shall not construct any LittleFS file path by directly concatenating a user-supplied URL parameter. All file access shall go through an allowlist of base directories (/missions, /logs) and an explicit filename validation step that rejects ".." sequences, leading slashes, and non-printable characters.
VERIFICATION: Inspection
RATIONALE: CERT-11 / REST-11. Prevents path traversal attacks that could expose or overwrite the checkpoint file, mission scripts, or other firmware data.
REFS: docs/standards/cert_standard.md CERT-11, docs/standards/apirest_standard.md REST-11

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-5003
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Storage, Boot, Health
STATEMENT: At boot, LittleFS shall be mounted and a filesystem health check performed. If mount fails, the firmware shall attempt to format and re-mount the partition. If re-mount also fails, the storage health flag in GET /api/status shall be set to false and all storage-dependent operations (AMS, logging, checkpoint) shall be disabled for the session.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: A corrupt filesystem must not cause undefined behaviour in file I/O calls. Graceful degradation to a storage-less mode allows the operator to inspect the failure via the REST API and decide whether to reflash.
REFS: docs/api/wifi_api_endpoints.md GET /api/status

